What is lazy loading in Angular ??

Lazy loading in angular is a technique where feature modules are loaded only when needed, instead of the application startup.
We configure it in the router using LoadChildren

const routes: Routes = [
{ path: 'customers',
loadChildren: () => import('./customers/customers.module').then(m => m.CustomersModule) }
];

